247
00:57:30,706 --> 00:57:32,833
<i>[Young Jack]</i>
<i>Nobody talks about it.</i>

248
00:57:37,245 --> 00:57:39,008
<i>Help me not to sass my dad.</i>

249
00:57:41,583 --> 00:57:44,677
Help me not to get dogs in fights.

250
00:57:58,934 --> 00:58:01,903
Help me be thankful for
everything I've got.

251
00:58:04,039 --> 00:58:06,166
<i>[Young Jack]</i> <i>Where do you live?</i>

252
00:58:07,209 --> 00:58:09,006
Help me not to tell lies.

253
00:58:16,752 --> 00:58:19,050
<i>[Whispering]</i>
<i>Are you watching me?</i>

254
00:58:19,154 --> 00:58:23,056
[Chattering, Shouting]

255
00:58:29,030 --> 00:58:31,157
<i>I want to know what you are.</i>

256
00:58:37,839 --> 00:58:40,364
<i>I want to see what you see.</i>

257
00:58:57,061 --> 00:59:00,462
<i>♪♪ [Organ]</i>

258
00:59:33,264 --> 00:59:35,562
- <i>[Father] Come here, youl</i>
- <i>[Boys Shouting]</i>

259
00:59:35,666 --> 00:59:38,658
- Come here. Come here, you!
- [Laughing]

260
00:59:40,704 --> 00:59:42,467
That funny?

261
00:59:44,542 --> 00:59:46,772
[Door Slams]

262
00:59:48,646 --> 00:59:52,309
You're gonna stand there, and you're
gonna close this door quietly 50 times.

263
00:59:53,751 --> 00:59:56,242
Count it out.

264
00:59:56,353 --> 00:59:59,413
Three, four...

265
00:59:59,523 --> 01:00:02,321
<i>five, six...</i>

266
01:00:02,426 --> 01:00:05,088
<i>seven, eight-</i>

267
01:00:05,196 --> 01:00:08,688
You can't just yank off the top.
You gotta get it by the root.

268
01:00:16,507 --> 01:00:18,475
- <i>[Father] Your mother's naive.</i>
- Whoa!

269
01:00:18,576 --> 01:00:21,374
<i>It takes fierce will to
get ahead in this world.</i>

270
01:00:23,013 --> 01:00:25,641
<i>If you're good,</i>
<i>people take advantage of you.</i>

271
01:00:32,056 --> 01:00:35,492
<i>Every one of these top executives-</i>
<i>you know how they got where they are?</i>

272
01:00:35,593 --> 01:00:39,154
- <i>Floated right down the middle of the river.</i>
- [Laughing]

273
01:00:40,564 --> 01:00:44,000
<i>Don't let anyone tell you</i>
<i>there's anything you can't do.</i>

274
01:00:45,836 --> 01:00:48,805
Don't do like I did. Promise me that.

275
01:00:50,875 --> 01:00:52,843
I dreamed of being a great musician.

276
01:00:53,878 --> 01:00:57,314
I let myself get sidetracked.

277
01:00:57,414 --> 01:01:00,110
If you're lookin' for somethin' to happen,
that was it.

278
01:01:00,217 --> 01:01:01,912
That was life. You lived it.

279
01:01:18,802 --> 01:01:22,898
<i>[Man] Job imagined</i>
<i>he might build his nest on high...</i>

280
01:01:23,007 --> 01:01:27,740
<i>that the integrity of his behavior</i>
<i>would protect him against misfortune.</i>

281
01:01:27,845 --> 01:01:29,745
<i>And his friends thought,
mistakenly...</i>

282
01:01:29,847 --> 01:01:32,577
that the Lord could only
have punished him...

283
01:01:32,683 --> 01:01:36,278
because secretly he'd done something wrong.

284
01:01:36,387 --> 01:01:37,877
But no.

285
01:01:37,988 --> 01:01:41,515
Misfortune befalls the good as well.

286
01:01:41,625 --> 01:01:43,786
We can't protect ourselves against it.

287
01:01:43,894 --> 01:01:46,362
We can't protect our children.

288
01:01:46,463 --> 01:01:49,296
We can't say to ourselves,
"Even if I'm not happy...

289
01:01:49,400 --> 01:01:52,130
I'm going to make sure they are."

290
01:01:52,236 --> 01:01:54,136
We run before the wind.

291
01:01:54,238 --> 01:01:56,968
We think that it will carry us forever.

292
01:01:57,074 --> 01:01:58,598
It will not.

293
01:01:58,709 --> 01:02:00,540
We vanish as a cloud.

294
01:02:00,644 --> 01:02:02,908
We wither as the autumn grass...

295
01:02:03,013 --> 01:02:06,278
and, like a tree, are rooted up.

296
01:02:08,419 --> 01:02:11,650
Is there some fraud
in the scheme of the universe?

297
01:02:11,755 --> 01:02:14,121
Is there nothing which is deathless...

298
01:02:14,224 --> 01:02:17,125
nothing which does not pass away?

299
01:02:19,263 --> 01:02:21,458
<i>We cannot stay where we are.</i>

300
01:02:21,565 --> 01:02:23,829
<i>We must journey forth.</i>

301
01:02:23,934 --> 01:02:28,371
<i>We must find that</i> <i>which is
greater than fortune or fate.</i>

302
01:02:29,406 --> 01:02:32,569
<i>Nothing can bring us peace but that.</i>

303
01:02:33,677 --> 01:02:36,840
<i>Is the body of the wise
man or the just...</i>

304
01:02:36,947 --> 01:02:38,847
<i>exempt from any pain...</i>

305
01:02:38,949 --> 01:02:41,042
<i>from any disquietude...</i>

306
01:02:41,151 --> 01:02:43,881
<i>from the deformity</i>
<i>that might blight its beauty...</i>

307
01:02:43,988 --> 01:02:47,116
<i>from the weakness</i>
<i>that might destroy its health?</i>

308
01:02:49,226 --> 01:02:52,059
<i>Do you trust in God?</i>

309
01:02:52,162 --> 01:02:55,893
<i>Job, too, was close to the Lord.</i>

310
01:02:56,000 --> 01:02:58,662
<i>Are your friends and
children your security?</i>

311
01:03:00,204 --> 01:03:02,434
<i>There is no hiding place
in all the world...</i>

312
01:03:02,539 --> 01:03:04,803
<i>where trouble may not find you.</i>

313
01:03:04,908 --> 01:03:07,672
<i>No one knows</i>
<i>when sorrow might visit his house...</i>

314
01:03:07,778 --> 01:03:10,872
<i>any more than Job did.</i>

315
01:03:10,981 --> 01:03:14,109
<i>The very moment everything</i>
<i>was taken away from Job...</i>

316
01:03:14,218 --> 01:03:17,346
<i>he knew it was the Lord
who'd taken it away.</i>

317
01:03:19,590 --> 01:03:22,582
<i>He turned from the
passing shows of time.</i>

318
01:03:22,693 --> 01:03:25,127
<i>He sought that which is eternal.</i>

319
01:03:26,563 --> 01:03:30,897
<i>Does he alone see God's hand</i>
<i>who sees that he gives?</i>

320
01:03:31,001 --> 01:03:33,026
<i>Or does not, also, the
one see God's hand-</i>

321
01:03:33,137 --> 01:03:36,629
- [Father] I'm your man.
- <i>Who sees that he takes away?</i>

322
01:03:36,740 --> 01:03:39,208
<i>Or does he alone see God...</i>

323
01:03:39,309 --> 01:03:41,470
<i>who sees God turn his
face towards him?</i>

324
01:03:43,480 --> 01:03:47,041
<i>Does not, also, he see God...</i>

325
01:03:47,151 --> 01:03:48,778
<i>who sees God turn his back?</i>

326
01:03:48,886 --> 01:03:51,719
That's a friend of mine.
He owns half the real estate in town.

327
01:03:53,924 --> 01:03:55,551
Frank Johnson.

328
01:03:56,593 --> 01:03:59,562
He started out as a barber.

329
01:04:00,831 --> 01:04:04,392
- But he built something big.
- [Laughing]

330
01:04:04,501 --> 01:04:07,561
Now you'd think he's the fourth person
of the holy Trinity.

331
01:04:09,706 --> 01:04:12,231
They never talk about their money.

332
01:04:15,145 --> 01:04:17,113
Wrong people go hungry...

333
01:04:18,749 --> 01:04:20,341
die.

334
01:04:22,453 --> 01:04:25,388
Wrong people get loved.

335
01:04:27,224 --> 01:04:29,215
The world lives by trickery.

336
01:04:32,096 --> 01:04:35,065
If you want to succeed,
you can't be too good.

337
01:04:42,606 --> 01:04:45,575
Hey there, young fellas.
How's it going today?

338
01:04:46,643 --> 01:04:48,611
Do y'all want some barbecue?

339
01:04:50,781 --> 01:04:52,976
[Father]
How about a pound of brisket?

340
01:05:20,410 --> 01:05:23,504
You're like this, right? Okay?
Come on. You act like you're scared.

341
01:05:23,614 --> 01:05:25,809
- You act like you're in trouble.
You don't wanna fight. - Nah.

342
01:05:25,916 --> 01:05:28,976
You don't want any trouble.
The minute you see him blink, crack him, okay?

343
01:05:29,086 --> 01:05:31,350
- Okay.
- Okay? Come on. Three quarters.

344
01:05:31,455 --> 01:05:34,481
Cover. You're gonna cover, right?
Okay. Hit it. Come on.

345
01:05:34,591 --> 01:05:37,822
Nice. Nice. Harder. Nice.
That's a good right. Let's see your left.

346
01:05:37,928 --> 01:05:40,522
That's the most important thing, okay?
You come in this way?

347
01:05:40,631 --> 01:05:43,464
You come in this way? You keep the guard up.
Hit me! Come on, hit me.

348
01:05:43,567 --> 01:05:48,004
Come on! Come on, Jack!
Hit me. Hit me. Hit me. Come on. Come on.

349
01:05:48,105 --> 01:05:51,370
Here. Here it is. Here it is.
Hit it. Come on, Son! Come on! Son.

350
01:05:51,475 --> 01:05:53,875
Left. What are you doing?

351
01:05:57,548 --> 01:06:00,381
Dust yourself off.

352
01:06:00,484 --> 01:06:03,942
Left. Don't leave your tongue out.
You're gonna lose it.

353
01:06:04,054 --> 01:06:06,079
Left. Left.

354
01:06:06,190 --> 01:06:07,919
Right. Right.

355
01:06:08,025 --> 01:06:11,483
Left. Harder. Harder. Harder!

356
01:06:11,595 --> 01:06:13,756
Come on, hit me. Hit me.

357
01:06:13,864 --> 01:06:16,526
Come on, Son. Hit it. Give me something.

358
01:06:16,633 --> 01:06:18,601
Show me what you got.

359
01:06:20,204 --> 01:06:22,195
Come on. Go on.

360
01:06:27,945 --> 01:06:29,572
[Father] One meal.

361
01:06:33,383 --> 01:06:35,010
[Murmurs]

362
01:06:42,326 --> 01:06:44,726
[Chuckling]

363
01:06:44,828 --> 01:06:46,728
Leave the table.

364
01:06:52,636 --> 01:06:54,263
You too?

365
01:06:55,939 --> 01:06:57,930
- You gonna continue to defy me?
- No, sir.

366
01:06:58,041 --> 01:07:01,067
You interrupted me. I wasn't done yet.

367
01:07:04,114 --> 01:07:05,877
Am I finished?

368
01:07:06,917 --> 01:07:08,544
May I?

369
01:07:09,720 --> 01:07:12,382
- [Grunts]
- Thank you, Your Majesty.

370
01:07:15,359 --> 01:07:20,194
<i>♪♪ [Piano]</i>

371
01:07:28,639 --> 01:07:31,608
♪♪ [Guitar]

372
01:08:08,912 --> 01:08:11,039
<i>[Young Jack Whispering]</i>
<i>Makes up stories.</i>

373
01:08:14,151 --> 01:08:16,051
<i>Original words.</i>

374
01:08:21,692 --> 01:08:24,024
- [Laughing]
- [Shouts]

375
01:08:24,127 --> 01:08:27,187
<i>He says,</i> <i>"Don't put
your elbows on the table."</i>

376
01:08:27,297 --> 01:08:29,094
Are you ready?

377
01:08:29,199 --> 01:08:31,099
<i>[Young Jack]</i> <i>He does.</i>

378
01:08:34,604 --> 01:08:36,504
<i>Insults people.</i>

379
01:08:37,974 --> 01:08:39,601
- <i>Doesn't care.</i>
- [Shouts]

380
01:08:39,710 --> 01:08:42,008
<i>[Father]</i>
<i>I remember when you were born.</i>

381
01:08:47,150 --> 01:08:49,118
They wouldn't let me come home.

382
01:08:50,887 --> 01:08:54,323
The navy said an officer must be present
for the laying of the keel...

383
01:08:54,424 --> 01:08:58,383
but... not at the launching.

384
01:09:28,792 --> 01:09:31,955
- [Shouting, Chattering]
- [Bell Clanging]

385
01:09:42,472 --> 01:09:44,702
[Man]
The next word is "volcano."

386
01:09:55,285 --> 01:09:57,276
The next word is "socket."

387
01:10:03,360 --> 01:10:07,160
Please pass your answers to each other.
We're gonna grade each other's papers now.

388
01:10:09,866 --> 01:10:12,892
[Laughing]

389
01:10:13,003 --> 01:10:14,903
[Teacher]
No interruptions, please.

390
01:10:15,005 --> 01:10:16,597
[Laughing Continues]

391
01:10:16,706 --> 01:10:19,174
Come on. Get your pencil out.

392
01:10:24,147 --> 01:10:26,615
After logs go to the paper mill...

393
01:10:29,820 --> 01:10:33,449
<i>♪♪ [Piano]</i>

394
01:11:05,055 --> 01:11:07,421
[Children Shouting]

395
01:11:26,009 --> 01:11:28,978
[Whistle Blowing]

396
01:11:39,823 --> 01:11:43,418
Taylor! Taylor, sweetheart!

397
01:11:43,527 --> 01:11:45,825
Honey! Honey!

398
01:11:52,736 --> 01:11:54,135
Let me go!

399
01:12:45,055 --> 01:12:47,353
<i>[Boys Laughing]</i>

400
01:13:01,104 --> 01:13:02,833
- [Screams]
- [Gasps]

401
01:13:14,184 --> 01:13:15,981
<i>[Young Jack]</i> <i>Was he bad?</i>

402
01:13:16,086 --> 01:13:19,055
[Children Shouting In Distance]

403
01:13:25,595 --> 01:13:28,063
[Youngest Brother]
Will you die too?

404
01:13:30,900 --> 01:13:33,391
<i>[Middle Brother]</i>
<i>You're not that old yet, Mom.</i>

405
01:13:51,121 --> 01:13:52,918
<i>[Young Jack]</i> <i>Where were you?</i>

406
01:14:05,135 --> 01:14:07,035
<i>You let a boy die.</i>

407
01:14:14,044 --> 01:14:16,512
<i>You'll let anything happen.</i>

408
01:14:29,793 --> 01:14:31,317
I can't see!

409
01:14:31,428 --> 01:14:33,225
I can't see!

410
01:14:36,933 --> 01:14:38,833
<i>[Young Jack]</i>
<i>Why should I be good...</i>

411
01:14:42,872 --> 01:14:45,500
<i>if you aren't?</i>

412
01:15:34,457 --> 01:15:36,084
Thank you.

413
01:15:50,807 --> 01:15:53,367
Too close.

414
01:15:53,476 --> 01:15:55,444
Edges.

415
01:15:55,545 --> 01:15:58,036
Why's this bare here, hmm?

416
01:15:58,148 --> 01:16:01,447
- Grass won't grow under the trees.
- Does at the Kimballs'.

417
01:16:01,551 --> 01:16:04,645
- They have a yardman.
- They have money.

418
01:16:04,754 --> 01:16:06,722
Course, he inherited it.

419
01:16:08,758 --> 01:16:12,159
I don't want to hear one more word out
of you, not till this is finished.

420
01:16:23,973 --> 01:16:25,531
Hmm?

421
01:16:26,576 --> 01:16:28,043
[Sniffles]

422
01:16:29,612 --> 01:16:31,170
Hmm?

423
01:16:53,069 --> 01:16:54,696
Cropping that too close.

424
01:16:54,804 --> 01:16:56,465
You're gonna have to keep that watered.

425
01:17:03,913 --> 01:17:05,813
Not high enough.

426
01:17:05,915 --> 01:17:07,883
[Whispers, Kissee]

427
01:17:11,621 --> 01:17:13,521
[Boys Laughing]

428
01:17:24,100 --> 01:17:25,965
Toscanini...

429
01:17:26,069 --> 01:17:28,264
once recorded a piece 65 times.

430
01:17:28,371 --> 01:17:30,771
You know what he said when he finished?

431
01:17:30,874 --> 01:17:32,899
"It could be better."

432
01:17:34,410 --> 01:17:36,037
Think about it.

433
01:17:38,615 --> 01:17:41,083
Twenty-seven patents your father has.

434
01:17:42,652 --> 01:17:45,553
<i>It means ownership.
Ownership of ideas.</i>

435
01:17:47,156 --> 01:17:49,420
<i>You gotta sew 'em up.
Get 'em by the nuts-</i>

436
01:17:49,525 --> 01:17:52,050
- We'll get 'em next time.
- <i>Pardon my French.</i>

437
01:17:52,161 --> 01:17:53,856
<i>[Father]</i> <i>We'll be rich.</i>

438
01:17:57,000 --> 01:17:59,468
<i>You make yourself what you are.</i>

439
01:18:03,072 --> 01:18:05,870
<i>You have control of
your own destiny.</i>

440
01:18:08,978 --> 01:18:10,946
<i>You can't say, "I can't."</i>

441
01:18:12,115 --> 01:18:14,015
<i>You say, "I'm having trouble.</i>

442
01:18:15,285 --> 01:18:17,014
I'm not done yet."

443
01:18:18,821 --> 01:18:21,255
<i>You can't say, "I can't."</i>

444
01:18:55,158 --> 01:18:57,353
<i>[Young Jack]</i>
<i>Why does he hurt us?</i>

445
01:18:59,696 --> 01:19:01,323
<i>Our father.</i>

446
01:19:07,303 --> 01:19:09,134
[Youngest Brother]
Come on, Dix. Come on!

447
01:19:09,238 --> 01:19:10,569
Ah, yeah. Get it! Get it!

448
01:19:24,854 --> 01:19:26,879
Give your father a kiss.

449
01:19:45,341 --> 01:19:47,809
<i>♪♪ [Piano]</i>

450
01:20:03,559 --> 01:20:06,027
- <i>♪♪ [Warped]</i>
- <i>[Father Chattering, Indistinct]</i>

451
01:20:06,129 --> 01:20:07,687
<i>[Young Jack]</i> <i>He lies.</i>

452
01:20:11,401 --> 01:20:13,699
- <i>Pretends.</i>
- Can you do something for me?

453
01:20:13,803 --> 01:20:16,237
You promise you'll do it
without having to ask what it is?

454
01:20:16,339 --> 01:20:18,967
Just have the confidence
that what your father asks of you is right?

455
01:20:19,075 --> 01:20:20,838
Yes, sir.

456
01:20:20,943 --> 01:20:25,642
For the next half hour, will you not speak
unless you have something important to say?

457
01:20:31,087 --> 01:20:33,555
What'd you do today,
my fine feathered friend?

458
01:20:35,425 --> 01:20:39,794
Sit on the front two inches of your chair.
Better for your posture.

459
01:20:39,896 --> 01:20:41,864
I read that in the paper.

460
01:20:45,001 --> 01:20:48,368
Did you actually buy this from Mr.
Ledbetter?

461
01:20:48,471 --> 01:20:51,099
Don't explain. Just nod- yes or no.

462
01:20:52,375 --> 01:20:54,002
- Hmm?
- No.

463
01:20:56,546 --> 01:20:57,843
Be quiet.

464
01:21:00,883 --> 01:21:02,851
What did you say?

465
01:21:05,655 --> 01:21:07,282
Please.

466
01:21:07,390 --> 01:21:09,017
- [Jack] Leave him alone!
- Come here!

467
01:21:09,125 --> 01:21:11,286
[Mother] Honey!

468
01:21:11,394 --> 01:21:14,852
- [Record Player Needle Scratches]
- Leave him alone!

469
01:21:18,201 --> 01:21:20,567
Come here! Get back. Come here.

470
01:21:24,907 --> 01:21:26,807
Get up there!

471
01:21:32,682 --> 01:21:35,310
[Slamming Furniture]

472
01:22:23,032 --> 01:22:24,761
You turned my own kids against me.

473
01:22:26,469 --> 01:22:28,403
You undermine everything I do.

474
01:22:37,680 --> 01:22:39,272
- How do you like-
- Stop...

475
01:22:40,116 --> 01:22:41,413
Stop it.

476
01:22:41,517 --> 01:22:44,645
Stop it! Stop. Stop it.

477
01:22:46,055 --> 01:22:47,989
[Sobs]

478
01:22:48,758 --> 01:22:50,089
Stop it.

479
01:22:53,029 --> 01:22:54,496
Stop it.

480
01:23:00,036 --> 01:23:02,163
Stop. Stop.

481
01:23:36,939 --> 01:23:39,908
[Sniffling, Crying]

482
01:23:40,009 --> 01:23:42,204
[Sprinkler Whirring, Hissing]

483
01:25:01,290 --> 01:25:03,155
Where's Dad?

484
01:25:03,259 --> 01:25:05,318
